Until 1917 Finland and the Baltic States had been part of Russia for several generations and regardless of what the people thought, when Mother Russia said "jump", the people of Finland were expected to say 'how high?'. Being naturally strong willed and physically imposing, the warriors of Finland prepared for a fight. A fight on their soil, in their homes. War breaks out.
